            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">How often should I update my content strategy?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Review quarterly, revise annually. Search intent shifts, competitors publish new pillar content, and product priorities change. A yearly full rewrite plus quarterly performance checks keeps the strategy alive.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between content strategy and content marketing?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Content strategy is the blueprint — audience, topics, formats, cadence, metrics. Content marketing is the execution — writing, publishing, promoting, and iterating. Strategy is the plan; marketing is the doing.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

